{center}
{subhead}Paul Nolan Joins Amiga{def}
{left}
{p} {p}
Amiga is committed to creating a user experience that will set the standard for
the future of digital living.
{p} {p}
As part of the first phase, we have brought together a renowned set of designers
and developers. We are delighted to announce that Paul Nolan will be joining the
corporate Amiga team. Paul comes to us with many years of experience in the
design and implementation of numerious graphics development and interface
products.
{p} {p}
"I`m excited to have the opportunity to help Amiga Inc. realize their dreams for
the next generation Amiga, and look forward to continuing to support the Amiga
community," Nolan said.
{p} {p}
{bold}About Amiga{nobold}
{p} {p}
Amiga defined multimedia and is currently defining the standards of the new
digital media reality with its products, the Amiga Software Development Kit and
the d'AMIGA Developer Workstation. These products allow developers to build the
next-generation digital media applications that will drive the connected world
in the very near future.
{p} {p}
{bold}About Paul Nolan{nobold}
{p} {p}
Paul Nolan, a distinguished application developer and graphics expert, is the
founder and CEO of Paul Nolan Software Inc., a San Diego, California based
company. His award-winning Photogenics graphics manipulation application has met
widespread acclaim since 1994 on the Classic Amiga, and will be soon be
available in stores across the country for Linux, too. More information on Paul
Nolan and the ongoing development of Photogenics can be found at
{link http://www.PaulNolan.com}www.PaulNolan.com{end}.
